{"author":{"id":"4511dff24612afd14b905af688103e1a80d66f065be7fd4f923752e66978583c"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1660738771,"nonce":"9lOWvQvmMstqeKL6/4fyCz8ntFI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOCGKeh85P-GQi","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/849","origin":"github"},"title":"Currate `stdout` and `stderr` in \"core\"","message":"As noted [a comment](https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug/issues/828#issuecomment-1185356084) in #828, the \"core\" of `git-bug` should support the CLI's need for parsable text output.  In order to enable this behavior, the \"core\" should have the following traits:\n\n- [ ] There should be no output to `stdout`\n- [ ] Minimize the amount of output to `stderr`\n- [ ] During \"core\" initialization, both `stdout` and `stderr` should be redirectable.\n- [ ] All error conditions should be returned to callers via Go `error`s without output to either `stdout` or `stderr`.","files":null}]}